column5: Hey all, thought I would post the info about this show for those that may not of heard about it. Dates are Nov 26, 27, & 28 at the International Centre Toronto.  Looks like a neat show.  We have a booth in Outdoor Canada Hall, if you are attending the show please swing by and say hello.  Outdoor Canada Show Link  Roland "WHOA SON" Martin and Jimmy "The bowl cut" Houston will be there as well.
I'll probably head down Saturday with my son as a test run for next years "spring" shows. I'll be solo, my wife goes down to Pennsylvania for Black Friday deals that weekend.

The presence of Roland and Jimmy doesn't improve the odds that I'll attend....but if Jeff (Gustaffson) and Gord (Pyzer) were there...THAT would get my attention.  But they'll probably be busy hauling in first ice 'eyes that weekend.
You mean I might meet you finally?  Friday will most likely be my day.
Woot Woot,  We will have a giant booth at the show as well.  I'll try to swing by if i get the chance.  I rather shake your hand then the boys down south lol.
I just went on the show link. Is there no archery dealers going? That sounds strange but the link shows none!

I'm not sure but there is a really good chance I'll be Smallie fishing, family Christmas Saturday afternoon, hoping to get out in the morning or at least Sunday for the day, last weekend til the end of June Richard

Yeah I don't blame ya Henry with all the bedbugs going on down there.  I hope so Brian, although I just want to make sure you know I was kidding around in some earlier posts lol  Would be nice for my partner Maureen to meet some more  "ofners".  I've been lucky to in the past already.
TOO LATE,,,,,,,,,,,,,J/K,,,,,,,,,,  Be nice to finaly meet ya bud.   Would it help the cause Phil?
LOL sorry Brian...Legend Boats will be at the show

Would help with some material anyways!!!  Here is one for ya Brian:  The National Poetry Contest had come down to two semi-finalists:  A Yale graduate, and a Newfoundlander. They were given a single word, then allowed two minutes to come up with a poem that contained the word.   The word they were given was ' TIMBUKTU '. The Yale graduate steps to the microphone and said:   'SLOWLY ACROSS THE DESERT SAND TREKKED A LONELY CARAVAN. MEN ON CAMELS, TWO BY TWO DESTINATION - TIMBUKTU '.   The crowd went crazy! No way could the Newfie top that, they thought.  The Newfoundlander calmly made his way to the microphone and recited:  'ME AND TIM A HUNTIN' WENT, MET T'REE LADIES IN A POP-UP TENT. DEY WAS T'REE, AND WE WAS TWO, SO I BUCKED ONE, AND TIMBUKTU '!  The Newfie won hands down.
Im heading to my blind by myself this afternoon,wonders ifder be t'ree wait,n for me.
Gord is going to be there  Here is a list of the whole schedule for the wknd  The Great Outdoors & DIY Weekend  I'm thinking about heading down for the day on Saturday, Looks interested
